{"parse":{"title":"Charles Lee (activist)","pageid":55471821,"revid":807204374,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Charles Lee</b> is an American <a href=\"/wiki/Environmental_justice\" title=\"Environmental justice\">environmental justice</a> activist and the senior policy advisor in the Office of Environmental Justice at the <a href=\"/wiki/Environmental_Protection_Agency\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Environmental Protection Agency\">Environmental Protection Agency</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-mfn_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-mfn-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Previously, he served as the director of the Office of Environmental Justice,<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and before that, he was the director of the Environmental Justice Program at the <a href=\"/wiki/United_Church_of_Christ\" title=\"United Church of Christ\">United Church of Christ</a> for 15 years.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ajph_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ajph-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>In 1987, the United Church of Christ released a report entitled <i>Toxic Wastes and Race in the United States</i>, of which Lee was the principal author. The report has been described as \"groundbreaking\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-mfn_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-mfn-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and as \"the first report to use rigorous analysis and methods to show how pollution and environmental hazards were disproportionately affecting minority and low-income communities.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-ajph_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ajph-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> It had a much more rapid impact than Lee had anticipated: within six years, all of its recommendations had been implemented.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ajph_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ajph-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Charles_Lee_(activist)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-mfn-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-mfn_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-mfn_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.movingforwardnetwork.com/2017/04/environmental-justice-leader-charles-lee-honored-by-the-state-of-south-carolina/\">\"Environmental justice leader Charles Lee honored by the State of South Carolina\"</a>. <i>Moving Forward Network</i>. 2017-04-04<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2017-10-07</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Moving+Forward+Network&amp;rft.atitle=Environmental+justice+leader+Charles+Lee+honored+by+the+State+of+South+Carolina&amp;rft.date=2017-04-04&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.movingforwardnetwork.com%2F2017%2F04%2Fenvironmental-justice-leader-charles-lee-honored-by-the-state-of-south-carolina%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACharles+Lee+%28activist%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://grist.org/climate-energy/heres-the-history-of-environmental-justice-summed-up-in-less-than-4-minutes/\">\"Here's the history of environmental justice, summed up in less than 4 minutes\"</a>. <i>Grist</i>. 2014-08-05<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2017-10-07</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Grist&amp;rft.atitle=Here%E2%80%99s+the+history+of+environmental+justice%2C+summed+up+in+less+than+4+minutes&amp;rft.date=2014-08-05&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fgrist.org%2Fclimate-energy%2Fheres-the-history-of-environmental-justice-summed-up-in-less-than-4-minutes%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACharles+Lee+%28activist%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-ajph-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-ajph_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ajph_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ajph_3-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Morrison, Dianne See (2009-11-01). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2774201\">\"Rallying Point: Charles Lee's Long-Standing Career in Environmental Justice\"</a>. <i>American Journal of Public Health</i>. <b>99</b> (Suppl 3): S508\u2013S510. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.2105/AJPH.2009.178590\">10.2105/AJPH.2009.178590</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Serial_Number\" title=\"International Standard Serial Number\">ISSN</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.worldcat.org/issn/0090-0036\">0090-0036</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/PubMed_Central\" title=\"PubMed Central\">PMC</a>&#160;<span class=\"plainlinks\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2774201\">2774201</a>&#8239;<img alt=\"Freely accessible\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/comm